{"questionId":"26529","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The strength of earthquakes is measured on the Richter magnitude scale, with values&nbsp;typically between&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;is the most severe.</p>\n<p>The Gutenberg–Richter equation gives the average number of earthquakes per year,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi></math>,&nbsp;which have a magnitude of at least&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math>. For a particular region the equation is</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mn>10</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>M</mi></math>, for some&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℝ</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>This region has an average of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn></math>&nbsp;earthquakes per year with a magnitude of at least&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>log</mi><mn>10</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mn>100</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26529","referenceCode":"22M.1